The '''Albany Medical Center Prize in Medicine and Biomedical Research''' is the ' highest value prize in medicine and biomedical research.  
The prize was established in 2000 from a US$50 million gift from late-Morris Silverman's Marty and Dorothy Silverman Foundation.  Among prizes for medicine, the Albany Medical Center Prize is second only to the $1.4 million . 
In 2008, the $500,000 prize was shared by Joan Steitz and Elizabeth Blackburn.